      "id": 999,
      "options": {
        "content": "# Load-Aware Cost Model\n\nThis dashboard uses **load-aware cost calculations** based on actual resource usage:\n\n**Compute Cost Formula:**\n```\ncompute_cost = sum_over_time(cpu_usage_cores[scenario]) \u00d7 PRICE_PER_CORE_SECOND\n```\n\n**Energy Cost Formula:**\n```\nenergy_joules = sum_over_time(power_watts \u00d7 step_seconds)\nenergy_cost = energy_joules \u00d7 PRICE_PER_JOULE\n```\n\n**Total Cost:**\n```\ntotal_cost = compute_cost + energy_cost\n```\n\n### Cost Scaling\n- \u2705 More streams \u2192 Higher CPU usage \u2192 Higher cost\n- \u2705 Higher bitrate \u2192 Higher CPU usage \u2192 Higher cost  \n- \u2705 Multi-resolution ladders \u2192 More pixels encoded \u2192 Higher cost\n- \u2705 Idle baseline \u2192 Minimal CPU usage \u2192 Lowest cost\n\nCosts are based on **real measurements** from Prometheus, not fixed wall-clock duration.\n",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "\u2139\ufe0f Load-Aware Cost Model",
      "type": "text"
    },
